# Chapter 2: Eligibility and Requirements (South Africa)

This chapter explains who can apply for a Code 10 driverâ€™s licence in South Africa
and what you need to prepare before starting the process.

## Minimum eligibility
- Age requirement
- Valid South African identification
- Any other general conditions required by the DLTC

## Documents you should prepare
- South African ID (or accepted identification)
- Proof of residential address (if your DLTC requires it)
- ID photos (if applicable)
- Completed application forms required by your testing centre

## Eyesight and medical considerations
Most applicants will complete an eyesight test at the DLTC. If you wear glasses or
contact lenses, bring them with you.

## When you may need a PrDP
If you intend to drive passengers or goods professionally, you may need a Professional
Driving Permit in addition to your Code 10 licence.

## Quick summary
By the time you finish this chapter, you should know exactly whether you qualify and
have a clear list of what to bring and prepare.

